RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 1 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 79. Maiden Optional Claiming Purse 40000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD THAT HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OR THAT WERE RNA OR SOLD AT AUCTION FOR $150,000 OR LESS OR CLAIMING $62,500-$50,000. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $62,500, For Each $6,250 To $50,000 1 lb. (For Eligibility Purposes, Refer To Most Recent Auction The Horse Was In).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SOUL OF A WARRIOR stalked the top pair up the backstretch, took aim three wide into the lane, moved out while rallying to catch the drifting leader, drew alongside that rival past the sixteenth pole and got up in time. UNJOKABLE dueled for command outside a rival, shook free at the top of the lane, drifted out under left-handed urging through the lane, led clear into deep stretch and got nailed in the final moments. SIDE BY SIDE hopped at the start, sat off the pace early off the inside, angled in for the turn, summoned a mild rally up the fence and gained the show. COLLECTMYTHOUGHTS dueled inside UNJOKABLE into and around the turn, could not keep up with that rival into the lane, stayed on through the final furlong and got edged for the show honors. LIL TOWN SIS tracked along the inside into the turn, moved out and exited the bend four wide, drifted out in the lane and kept on while unable to threaten. SWEET MOTHER MARY chased from off the pace, went four wide into the turn, three wide into the lane, wanted to go outside LIL TOWN SIS then altered back inward in upper stretch and could not rally. PRINCESS MAGIC broke out then was hard to ride up the backstretch, trailed three then two wide on the turn and failed to menace.
